        <abstract> 
<p>Concern over Wallace’s book [<hi rend="italic">Contributions to the theory of natural selection</hi> (1870)] and its apparent backsliding from Darwinian theory. HWB suggests that only CD is capable of criticising the book.</p>  
<p>HWB hopes not too much was made over his few comments on man in M. F. Somerville’s book [<hi rend="italic">Physical geography</hi>, revised ed. (1870)].</p> 
